Feeder load profiles for the three cases
As shown in subplot 1, Fig. 15, in the perfect-forecast case, the PEESS can compensate for the feeder load fluctuations well (with one overshoot at 13.8) without being turned on and off very frequently (as shown in Fig. 17). The room temperatures are maintained within the desired range (subplot 1, Fig. 16).Fig. 16
Impact of different forecasting accuracies of the feeder baseline load on room temperature profiles
As shown in subplots 2 and 3, Fig. 15, in the over-forecast or under-forecast cases, the PEESS has multiple overshoots or undershoots from PfBaseline\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
